summary: This is an automated out-of-office email reply from a federal prosecutor, indicating they will be unavailable until January 5, 2020, and directing urgent matters to other Assistant U.S. Attorneys on the Epstein case. It shows ongoing case activity and coordination among prosecutors in early 2020.
keyFacts: The email is an automatic out-of-office reply dated January 5, 2020.
The sender is a federal prosecutor (AUSA) working on the Epstein investigation.
The email indicates the Epstein case was active and being handled by multiple Assistant U.S. Attorneys as of early 2020.
The sender states they will have limited email access but can be reached for urgent matters through other AUSAs on the case.
